originalText.text:
⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
LONG BUT HONEST REVIEW:
I can't say enough good things about Victoria, the physical therapist extraordinaire! If you're in search of someone who is not only incredibly effective but also incredibly compassionate, look no further. Victoria is the best physical therapist I've ever had the pleasure of working with, and I can confidently say she's perfect for people with chronic ailments, like myself.

From the moment we began working together, I felt welcomed and valued. Victoria's warm and friendly demeanor instantly put me at ease, which is no small feat when you're dealing with health challenges. She truly listens and takes the time to understand your unique needs and concerns, making you feel like a partner in your own healthcare journey.

What sets Victoria apart, however, is her unparalleled skill and expertise. She has a deep understanding of the complexities of physical therapy, ESPECIALLY when it comes to working with individuals who have disabilities. Her treatments are not one-size-fits-all; instead, she tailors each session to address your specific issues and goals. Victoria's knowledge is vast, and she's always up-to-date with the latest advancements in her field.

But it's not just her knowledge and technical prowess that make her exceptional; it's her heart. Victoria genuinely cares about her patients. She celebrates your victories, no matter how small, and provides unwavering support during the tough times. She's a true motivator, always pushing you to be your best self.

Thanks to Victoria's guidance and expertise, I've made remarkable progress on my journey towards improved mobility and overall well-being. She's not just a physical therapist; she's a friend, a mentor, and a source of inspiration.

If you're in need of a physical therapist who is compassionate, skilled, and perfect for individuals with disabilities, I wholeheartedly recommend Victoria. She's a true gem in her profession, and I'm incredibly grateful to have her as my therapist. I couldn't have asked for a better partner in my healing journey. She is, HANDS DOWN, better than all the physical therapist I've ever worked with COMBINED.. and I've worked with 10+ doctors over 15 years.

Thank you, Victoria, for being the best physical therapist ever! You truly have made a tangible impact on decreasing my daily levels of chronic pain. I am forever grateful my insurance fell into your network!!!

originalText.text: Victoria is a wonderful physical therapist and also a very kind person! She's clearly an expert at what she does, it took her no time at all to figure out my issues from an old injury, and the PT program she prescribed has been quite effective. Highly recommend!

originalText.text:
I have been working with Victoria for a few years now and I cannot say enough good things about her work, professionalism and bedside matter. She has helped me rehab both current injuries/surgeries and maintain more chronic issues stemming from years of beating up my body and a degenerative condition. I feel supported for success through body work, strength exercises and an increased awareness of where my body is in space at any given moment, connecting physical to pain to seemingly unrelated issues elsewhere in my body and putting forth reasonable “homework” that I can continue with when more formal PT is no longer needed. I also find her wealth of knowledge reassuring in the ways she conveys the what, how, now and future in non technical and relatable terms to really understand my treatment as part of the whole vs simply addressing the specific issue at hand.

10/10 recommend

originalText.text: Victoria has lived about nine lives before becoming a physical therapist, and brings her knowledge from all of these experiences to her practice. She is kind and caring and a really good listener (yes, I know you’re coming here for her medical qualifications, but I think these are under-appreciated aspects of a good practitioner!) My PT intake session with her was several hours. Honestly the most careful and intensive look anyone has taken at my body! She then crafted individualized ideas for workouts, and always has modifications and tweaks as I’ve started to do the exercises and noticed what does and doesn’t feel good. She has helped me listen to my body, and to be more confident and intentional in my movements. I wish she could train my other doctors because this is a kind of medical care we all wish we were getting!
